  "Siblings Kuldip and Gurbachan Singh Dhingra control Berger Paints India, the country's second-large paint maker. ",
  "In 1991 they bought Berger Paints, then the country's smallest player from controversial liquor tycoon Vijay Mallya. ",
  "Apart from India, Berger has a presence in Russia, Nepal, Bangladesh and Poland. ",
  "Two of their children sit on Berger's board and are being groomed to succeed."
